Span.Text: Time is the most valuable resource
for my clinicians.  Help us save time
I need simplified, connected, sustainable, intelligent information
my teams to be mobile and connected

“Improve quality of care and patient safety, reduce costs, treat more patients for less, close beds, improve outcomes, be an effective management team, pass CQC audits….  which one are you losing sleep over?"¬
Suzy Foster, Director Health and Life Sciences, Microsoft UK

In a digital, mobile world, it seems crazy that communicating between staff, colleagues and patients across the care pathway in the NHS is so difficult.  The technology already exists to enable efficient communication, we just need to embrace it in healthcare.
Empower care teams with fast, easy ways to communicate
Enable health professionals to communicate easily with their colleagues using email, IM and voice.
Now clinicians can video conference and send instant messages with patients too, on Skype or Lync, right from within Office.

With Yammer enterprise social capabilities built into Office 365, your health teams have a flexible, collaborative workspace to get work done wherever and whenever.   Yammer allows you to have working groups to allow easy conversations and communication across the healthcare system.

Being able to communicate with clinicians and community nurses from their own home saves time, money and most importantly is best for some patients.  Lync and Skype For Business can make a huge difference to how care in the community can function efficiently.  There are also a range of apps available that patients can use to manage their own care plans, and connect with other patients.

With native Office applications such as Word and Excel for iPad, iOS and Android, health professionals can increase productivity using almost any device they choose, from PCs to smartphones to tablets. Office 365 can save files automatically to the cloud, so notes you make are accessible almost immediately from anywhere. Formatting remains intact regardless no matter what device you’re using.
"Using the communication and collaboration features in Lync 2010 within a clinical environment, we can expedite the decision-making process."
Paul Duffy, Chief Information Officer, Belfast Health and Social Care Trust
Belfast Health and Social Care Trust improve workflow and communications to help doctors and nurses connect more efficiently and deliver higher levels of care, using Microsoft Lync.

"Video consultation enables GPs and Consultants to sit in one office and deal with many more patients, their problems, and help their families."
Dr Chris Jones, Programme Director, West Wakefield Health & Wellbeing
West Wakefield Health and Wellbeing have increased patient care hours and improved access to health resources using Microsoft Lync.

BI has taken off tremendously in the NHS in the past few years.  It can provide actionable intelligent data, for frontline staff and managers, to make real changes.  However, implementation, data linkage and maintaining software can be extremely difficult and costly.  Using familiar coding and Microsoft based products ensures sustainability in-house and keeps external contractors costs to a minimum.

Mine disparate information systems to build more accurate and richer patient profiles. With the ability to fuse structured data (e.g., electronic health records) with unstructured data (e.g., handwritten case notes), you can uncover previously hidden intelligence.
Glean insight quickly from multiple data types

Optimise diagnosis and treatment using highly intuitive, interactive data exploration, visualisation and presentation for all health professional skill levels. Ask questions in a natural-language speech bubble, and Microsoft Excel answers by generating appropriate data visualisations.
Working together is easy with integrated sharing capabilities in Excel. Post analyses to social networks, present findings online or send workbooks via instant message.

Uncover unexpected patterns and associations and develop models to anticipate emerging health trends. Use predictive data to develop targeted population health strategies and help cut health costs at city, provider and systemic levels.
"Linking data for analyses was something we couldn’t do before. With Power BI, it’s simple. Power BI makes the hard things easy. Everything becomes possible."
Professor Philip Dean, Head of Department of Pharmacy and Quality Control Laboratory Services,
North Tees and Hartlepool National Health Services Trust
UK Hospital Sees Cloud-Based BI Service as a Tool to Boost Clinical Outcomes and Efficiency

There are many different descriptions of what Cloud computing is, but a very simple explanation is that it means you can access your systems, data and documents from the Internet rather than from your computer. This means that you can access your information from virtually anywhere.  Embrace the cloud to become agile and connected, whilst being confident of compliance with IG and data security.

Reduce storage costs by 60% to 80%, versus traditional storage methods using StorSimple, an on-premises tiered storage appliance that delivers high performance storage, live archiving and cloud data protection.
How can the cloud benefit our patients?

The cloud opens up a world of opportunities to benefit the patient.  With wearable devices allowing patients to own, track and manage their care plans, the cloud provides the connecting engine for mobile monitoring from anywhere.

Azure has received OFFICIAL accreditation from the UK Government Pan Government Accreditor covering NHS trusts who hold or transact public sector data for business conducted at the OFFICIAL level of Security Classification.  The OFFICIAL accreditation forms part of the UK Government’s Cloud Security Principles.
How can the cloud benefit our clinicians?

Clinicians need to be able to access data from virtually anywhere, from any device. Cloud based technologies enable this to happen.  It also makes connecting and working with peers across the world easy, see how our technology has helped Operation Smile.
"I feel that our data is more secure with Microsoft Azure than if stored in our own building, and our lives have been much easier since we made the move to Azure."
Darren McVee, E-enablement Manager, East of England Collaborative Procurement Hub

Moving to a cloud-based solution has improved the day-to-day operations at the Hub by providing increased scalability for the organization to grow. It has also improved collaboration, provided more control, and saved considerable costs.

Your most valuable resource is your time.  Mobile devices are simple tools that give you more time to care, and mean less time is spent on sourcing information and completing administration.
With devices that staff love and the latest Windows operating system, clinicians and carers can spend more of their days (and nights) addressing patients’ real-time needs and less on admin.
All of your information in one place
With a large range of clinically relevant apps available on your portable device, you can access a range of information right where you need it.
Click to view our example of Onco Assist.
Benefits of using the device for the patient

Not only are devices vital for providing staff with a more efficient data access point.  The benefits are endless for the patient too. From improving patient feedback with bed side access of devices for entertainment, to uses in consultations, self management apps, and connecting the patient to relatives and family.
Click to see Microsoft's vision of how devices can help, when the human touch is not possible.
Access your data and information from virtually anywhere

When working from a range of devices all running off of a Windows platform, the possibilities to access your desktop and key information is endless.  Nurses and Clinicians are now being able to access and complete administration, looks at notes, and fill in forms at the bed side.
“The fact that we can jot notes easily using a digital pen on a responsive device capturing that data, is something that could revolutionise our practice.”
Dr Maida Chen, Medical Director Sleep Disorders, Seattle Childrens Hospital
One way Seattle Children's Hospital is addressing the growing need for clinicians to have instant and secure mobile access to patient health records, is through the full power of Surface Pro 3
